						               													<description>THE GREATEST RACING GAME SYSTEM NEVER DONE.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Racing Simulator is a racing car game for 1 to 9 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The system of game is simple but sophisticated, cars follow each other in single tail (1 car by space), simultaneously all the players reveal 1 speed card.&amp;#10;From the last car we are going to look by comparing speeds and place on the track if a car can overtake, decrease or increase the gap with the car which precedes it, and so on up to the lead car.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every player possesses potentially the same Speed cards as his opponents, but does not know what are going to make for every turn, cars forward and behind him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Add Bonus/malus dependings on the tyres type/condition, and the Action cards played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is excellent because the player finds himsef with exactly the same management problems of his tyres and his pitstops that the driver in the reality. According to the quality of tyres supplied by the manufacturer, and the course of the race, what is the best ? 1, 2, 3 or 4 pitstops (Hard or soft tyres) !!!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cars not attributed to a player are managed by the system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The races are governed by the real F1 rules.&amp;#10;Qualifications, start in grid, launched start, change of tyres (1 to 4 pitstop opportunities dependings the tyres delivered by the manufacturer), quality and wear of tyres, rain, track humidity level, incidents, accidents, penalties, safety car, everything is simulated with simple rules easy to implement.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 party lasts approximately 1 hours 30 (40 minutes for the Family game).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
